    {
        "content": "<p>(Regarding the convention for base change, I'm pretty sure most mathematical texts have incoherent conventions, and in any case, most authors are incoherent from one text to another. So mathlib can fix one, I see no harm in that.)</p>",
        "id": 477303209,
        "sender_full_name": "Antoine Chambert-Loir",
        "timestamp": 1729113970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I might be missing the point above, but it seems to me there is also a \"natural\" way to get the usual <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\frac{az + b}{cz + d}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2834em;vertical-align:-0.4033em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8801em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.655em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">cz</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">d</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.394em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">b</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.4033em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span> formula.</p>\n<p>If we start with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">P</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{CP}^1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8929em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">CP</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8929em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1418em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> but also endow it with the real structure coming from complex conjugation then its automorphism group <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>L</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">PSL(2, \\mathbb{C})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">PS</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> has a distinguished <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>L</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">PSL(2, \\mathbb{R})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">PS</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> which has three orbits. The boring one, fixed by the real structure, is <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">P</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{RP}^1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8929em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">RP</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8929em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1418em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, but the other two, interchanged by the real structure, are interesting. If we consider the orbit containing <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mi>i</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">[i, 1]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span> then we get the usual <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\frac{az + b}{cz + d}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2834em;vertical-align:-0.4033em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8801em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.655em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">cz</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">d</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.394em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.04398em;\">z</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">b</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.4033em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span> formula, right?</p>",
